    "course_title": "AFRICAN AMERICAN WOMEN'S ACTIVISM (19TH & 20TH CENTURIES)",
    "description": "Examines Black women's struggles for racial justices; reconsiders conventional notions of leadership, politics and protest. Topics include abolitionism, anti-lynching campaigns, woman suffrage, labor movement, club movement, cultural expressions, civil rights protest, Black feminism/womanism, poverty and welfare rights, environmental racism, etc.",
